text: The 2016 United States presidential election in Pennsylvania took place on November 8, 2016, as part of the 2016 United States presidential election. Pennsylvania has 20 electoral votes in the Electoral College. Obama won the state in 2012 by a margin of 5.38%. However, Trump was able to get back the state, winning it by a 0.72% margin. ==References== Category:2016 United States presidential election
title: 2016 United States presidential election in Pennsylvania
